``` javascript
 function*fibonacci() {
    var pre = 0, cur = 1;
    for (;;) {
      var temp = pre;
      pre = cur;
      cur += temp;
      yield cur;
    }
  }
var it = fibonacci();
for (var n of it) {
  // truncate the sequence at 1000
  if (n > 1000)
    break;
  console.log(n);
}
```
- set a breakpoint on the console log
- run program and when stopped hover of `it`
  -> The variables view, watch and debug console all render it as 'Generator'. Hover just shows 'proto'

